{"app_type": "privileged", "author": "Mossroy <mossroy@free.fr>", "banner_message": null, "banner_regions": [], "categories": ["books", "education"], "content_ratings": {"regions": {"co": "esrb", "ve": "esrb", "cl": "esrb", "de": "usk", "it": "pegi", "us": "esrb", "hu": "pegi", "br": "classind", "ar": "esrb", "es": "pegi", "uk": "pegi", "pe": "esrb", "uy": "esrb", "mx": "esrb", "pl": "pegi", "gr": "pegi"}, "ratings": null, "interactive_elements": null, "descriptors": null}, "created": "2013-08-23T11:36:10", "current_version": "1.0.3", "default_locale": "en-US", "description": {"en-US": "<b>Offline Wikipedia Viewer</b>\n\nYou can read <b>all</b> the wikipedia content (except images) without Internet access (no 3G, no WiFi).\nIf your Internet access is expensive/rare/slow/unreliable/watched/censored, you still can browse this amazing amount of knowledge and culture.\nFor this application to work, an archive of wikipedia has to be downloaded first, and stored on the SD-card (see below or in the About section of the application)\n\nOfficial site : <a href=\"http://outgoing.mozilla.org/v1/629e835199bc5dad1a6ba70c8a2311e8811e8559a227e621b086d537687a0238/http%3A//www.evopedia.info/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.evopedia.info/</a>\n\nYou can search among the article titles, and read any of them, all this offline.\nAll the content of wikipedia is inside your device (except the images). It also works with Wiktionary and Wikivoyage.\n\nNB : If you're connected to the Internet when using the application, the images of the articles will be displayed from the Internet. \n\n<b>You have to first download an archive of wikipedia and put it on your SD-card</b>\nThe archives can be downloaded (with a Bittorrent client, on a regular computer) at <a href=\"http://outgoing.mozilla.org/v1/d3cbe45b9ccda53e263d012bb9d4a4992e65d3339d77ed751de8cdbb824589fa/http%3A//dumpathome.evopedia.info/dumps/finished\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://dumpathome.evopedia.info/dumps/finished</a>\nThe content has to be put in any subdirectory of your SD-card (ex : /evopedia/wikipedia_en_2012-02-11). Check that your SD-card is large enough because each archive takes several GB.\nThen run the application : it will scan and find the archives on the SD-card and let you use them.\n\nThe source code of this application is released under GPL v3 license"}, "device_types": ["firefoxos"], "homepage": {"en-US": "http://www.evopedia.info/"}, "icons": {"16": "https://marketplace.cdn.mozilla.net/img/uploads/addon_icons/461/461357-32.png?modified=1388532743", "48": "https://marketplace.cdn.mozilla.net/img/uploads/addon_icons/461/461357-48.png?modified=1388532743", "128": "https://marketplace.cdn.mozilla.net/img/uploads/addon_icons/461/461357-128.png?modified=1388532743", "64": "https://marketplace.cdn.mozilla.net/img/uploads/addon_icons/461/461357-64.png?modified=1388532743"}, "id": 461357, "is_packaged": true, "manifest_url": "https://marketplace.firefox.com/app/d5f926ee-b7b4-48ab-8b99-a56079e654b0/manifest.webapp", "name": {"en-US": "Evopedia"}, "payment_account": null, "payment_required": false, "premium_type": "free", "previews": [{"filetype": "image/png", "image_url": "https://marketplace.cdn.mozilla.net/img/uploads/previews/full/111/111496.png?modified=1377797002", "id": 111496, "resource_uri": null, "thumbnail_url": "https://marketplace.cdn.mozilla.net/img/uploads/previews/thumbs/111/111496.png?modified=1377797002"}, {"filetype": "image/png", "image_url": "https://marketplace.cdn.mozilla.net/img/uploads/previews/full/111/111498.png?modified=1377797002", "id": 111498, "resource_uri": null, "thumbnail_url": "https://marketplace.cdn.mozilla.net/img/uploads/previews/thumbs/111/111498.png?modified=1377797002"}, {"filetype": "image/png", "image_url": "https://marketplace.cdn.mozilla.net/img/uploads/previews/full/111/111501.png?modified=1377797002", "id": 111501, "resource_uri": null, "thumbnail_url": "https://marketplace.cdn.mozilla.net/img/uploads/previews/thumbs/111/111501.png?modified=13